        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme \"Dr. Syama Prasad Mookerjee Durghtana Sahayta Yojana\" by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department, Haryana , aims to provide financial assistance of ₹1,00,000 in case of accidental death or disability to residents of Haryana who are not enrolled under the PMSBY.",
        "detailedDescription_md": "Launched in 2017, the &amp;quot;Dr. Syama Prasad Mookerjee Durghtana Sahayta Yojana&amp;quot; is a state-level welfare scheme of the Government of Haryana under the Social Justice and Empowerment Department. It provides financial assistance of ₹1,00,000/- to individuals between 18 and 70 years of age who have suffered accidental death or disability and are not registered under the Pradhan Mantri Suraksha Bima Yojana (PMSBY). The scheme is applicable only to permanent residents of Haryana residing in the state. The scheme is implemented by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department.\n",
        "benefits_md": "> **Monetary Benefit:**  ₹1,00,000/- is provided in case of:\n\n\n- Accidental death.\n- Total and permanent loss of both eyes.\n- Loss of both hands or both feet.\n- Loss of one eye and one hand or one foot.\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "\n- The applicant should not be registered under the Pradhan Mantri Suraksha Bima Yojana (PMSBY).\n\n<br>\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "detailedDescription": [
          {
            "type": "align_justify",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Launched in 2017, the \"Dr. Syama Prasad Mookerjee Durghtana Sahayta Yojana\" is a state-level welfare scheme of the Government of Haryana under the Social Justice and Empowerment Department. It provides financial assistance of ₹1,00,000/- to individuals between 18 and 70 years of age who have suffered accidental death or disability and are not registered under the Pradhan Mantri Suraksha Bima Yojana (PMSBY). The scheme is applicable only to permanent residents of Haryana residing in the state. The scheme is implemented by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
